  "commentary": "With SPX at 6528.64 sitting below the GEX flip at 6544, dealers are in positive gamma territory and will mechanically sell any rally toward the massive 6550 wall (7.2B) while providing support on dips toward the 6500 negative gamma wall (-8.5B). The PIN regime combined with the gex_surge event suggests dealers are aggressively hedging into this move, creating a tight 6500-6550 range where mean reversion should dominate with dealers acting as liquidity providers. Watch for rejection at 6545-6550 resistance cluster and strong buying interest if we test the 6500 amplifying level where dealer hedging flips to momentum-adding.",
